WEBVTT

00:01.601 --> 00:04.537
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

00:04.604 --> 00:11.611
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.245 --> 00:14.881
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:16.449 --> 00:18.451
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.518 --> 00:24.524
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.591 --> 00:27.193
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:32.932 --> 00:35.502
- Okay, so this is
a game I made up.

00:35.568 --> 00:37.470
I don't have
a catchy title yet,

00:37.537 --> 00:41.408
but it's like hide and seek,
except you yell a pasta dish

00:41.474 --> 00:43.209
when you find someone.
- Ooh!

00:43.276 --> 00:46.179
What if we call it,
"Ready Spaghetti"?

00:46.246 --> 00:47.981
- Yes!
- And you gotta wear

00:48.047 --> 00:50.183
a bug on your head.
- No!

00:50.250 --> 00:52.252
- Mine's laying eggs.

00:52.318 --> 00:55.355
- One, two three,
ready spaghetti!

00:57.390 --> 00:58.491
Tagliatelle!

00:58.558 --> 01:01.060
{\an1}- [laughs]

01:01.127 --> 01:03.029
- Pad Thai!

01:03.096 --> 01:04.563
- Mac 'n cheese!

01:04.631 --> 01:05.932
- Lasagna Bolognaise!

01:05.999 --> 01:07.400
- Dandan noodles!

01:07.467 --> 01:08.968
{\an3}- Kugel!

01:09.035 --> 01:10.637
- Pasta al carbone!

01:10.703 --> 01:11.838
- Blargle gargle!

01:11.905 --> 01:15.108
- Fettucine Alfre...do.

01:15.175 --> 01:17.710
- Excuse please, little girl.

01:17.777 --> 01:20.079
Have you seen these two babies?

01:23.783 --> 01:26.553
- Mom? Dad?

01:29.856 --> 01:31.090
{\an1}- Ohh!

01:31.157 --> 01:34.093
<i>[light music]</i>

01:34.160 --> 01:41.401
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:42.502 --> 01:44.771
- [munching]

01:44.838 --> 01:46.973
- Little babies grow so big!

01:47.040 --> 01:48.975
Who knew babies do that?

01:49.042 --> 01:50.910
- Thank you, Beakses, for food.

01:50.977 --> 01:53.613
- No, thank you.
I've been dying to try out

01:53.680 --> 01:55.482
that new scone recipe.

01:55.548 --> 01:58.051
Fee, are you sure
you're comfortable over--

01:58.117 --> 02:00.854
- Yeah I'm cool thanks.
[bell dings]

02:00.920 --> 02:04.090
{\an3}- Ooh! Who's excited
for crumpets?

02:04.157 --> 02:06.826
- So, Bada--
- I Bada.

02:06.893 --> 02:08.495
- I Grada.
- I Foo!

02:08.561 --> 02:10.229
{\an3}- You have
an interesting accent.

02:10.295 --> 02:11.598
- Where are you two from?

02:11.664 --> 02:14.901
{\an3}- We live in Greater
Impland Empire.

02:14.968 --> 02:17.937
{\an1}- Is very nice.
Lots of bees.

02:18.004 --> 02:19.539
- Yes. So many bees.

02:19.606 --> 02:22.175
{\an3}Oh, before I do forget,
I want to give gift.

02:22.242 --> 02:26.412
{\an1}- Yes, thank you for taking care
of our babies.

02:27.413 --> 02:29.516
- [laughs] Really, you didn't
have to--ahh! Ahh!

02:29.582 --> 02:31.050
Snakes! Snakes!

02:31.117 --> 02:33.753
- In Impland Empire,
snakes are for money.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.255
- [grunting]

02:35.321 --> 02:38.391
- Mommy? Daddy? What do you guys
do for a living?

02:38.458 --> 02:43.062
{\an1}- Well, little baby Foo,
your Papa is artist.

02:43.129 --> 02:47.000
- I am whittler.
These are my whittle treasures.

02:47.066 --> 02:48.701
This is tiny house!

02:48.768 --> 02:50.270
Cost one snake.

02:50.336 --> 02:52.505
And this is tiny elephant.

02:52.572 --> 02:54.274
Cost one snake.

02:54.340 --> 02:56.576
And this is tiny snake.

02:56.643 --> 02:58.011
Cost two snake.

02:58.077 --> 03:00.146
- There's blood on those.
- No, no, no.

03:00.213 --> 03:02.382
That is creative juices
from hands.

03:02.448 --> 03:05.151
Sometimes I get so creative
I get woozy.

03:05.218 --> 03:08.021
- And I am accountant.

03:08.087 --> 03:09.822
- Uh--oh really?

03:09.889 --> 03:12.692
- Yes, I best accountant.

03:12.759 --> 03:16.162
One, two, three, four,

03:16.229 --> 03:19.432
five, six, seven, eight...
- She very good.

03:19.499 --> 03:23.303
- ...9, 10, 11--
- Knock it off!

03:24.404 --> 03:26.906
All I wanna know is
where have you two been, huh?

03:26.973 --> 03:29.576
Why'd you leave Foo and me
all alone for so long?

03:29.642 --> 03:32.145
And now I'm supposed to be like,
"Oh hi, how's it going?

03:32.211 --> 03:35.214
Everything's cool."
- Crumpets anyone?

03:35.281 --> 03:38.251
{\an3}Bad time?
Okay I'll come back.

03:39.686 --> 03:40.987
- We didn't leave you.

03:41.054 --> 03:43.957
- You leave us.
- Huh?

03:44.023 --> 03:47.393
{\an1}- I tell you very serious
story now.

03:47.460 --> 03:49.729
both: Whoopa doopa!
Whoopa doopa! Whoopa doopa!

03:49.796 --> 03:50.997
- What are you doing?

03:51.064 --> 03:52.966
- Traditional Impland Empire

03:53.032 --> 03:55.001
story beginning festivities.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.736
- Maybe skip that part.

03:56.803 --> 03:58.805
- So no ham juggling?

03:58.871 --> 04:02.342
- No, just tell me
what happened. Please.

04:02.408 --> 04:06.746
- Okay. Was a beautiful
Harumday.

04:06.813 --> 04:08.681
<i>Business had been</i>
<i>very good.</i>

04:08.748 --> 04:12.118
<i>So house</i>
<i>was full of snakes.</i>

04:12.185 --> 04:16.356
[screaming, panting]

04:16.422 --> 04:20.459
<i>Grada and I decide to go</i>
<i>look for more anti-venom plants.</i>

04:20.526 --> 04:23.663
- Are my babies most comfy?
[laughing]

04:23.730 --> 04:27.133
<i>- Now everyone knows</i>
<i>best anti-venom plants</i>

04:27.200 --> 04:31.671
<i>grow at top of very tall</i>
<i>Mt. Khalkalash.</i>

04:31.738 --> 04:34.440
<i>And of course,</i>
<i>once you climb mountain,</i>

04:34.507 --> 04:36.376
<i>the first thing</i>
<i>you must do</i>

04:36.442 --> 04:40.146
<i>is traditional mountain climb</i>
<i>yoga stretches.</i>

04:42.315 --> 04:46.185
- Okay, babies,
now we not get cramps.

04:46.252 --> 04:48.421
Babies? Babies?!

04:48.488 --> 04:51.891
{\an3}Husband!
Babies go missing!

04:51.958 --> 04:54.694
- Maybe they fly?

04:54.761 --> 04:56.529
[both giggling]

04:56.596 --> 04:59.332
{\an3}- Wait. Only babies
with wings fly.

04:59.399 --> 05:02.402
- Do our babies have wings?
- Mm, no.

05:02.468 --> 05:04.470
- Then they must still
be up on mountain top.

05:04.537 --> 05:08.307
- I go this way.
You go that way.

05:09.175 --> 05:10.143
Find them?
- No.

05:10.209 --> 05:12.245
- Okay, we keep looking!

05:12.311 --> 05:14.547
- Find them?
- No.

05:14.614 --> 05:15.548
- Find them?

05:15.615 --> 05:16.482
{\an1}- No.

05:16.549 --> 05:18.217
- Find them?
- No.

05:18.284 --> 05:20.053
- How many times did
you circle that mountain?

05:20.119 --> 05:23.623
- Ah just 15 or 20...thousand.

05:23.690 --> 05:26.826
- I account them all.
- Winters were hardest.

05:26.893 --> 05:30.663
I lose toe.
- We eventually leave mountain,

05:30.730 --> 05:35.868
{\an1}but we never ever, ever
stop searching for our babies.

05:35.935 --> 05:37.136
{\an3}- [laughs]

05:37.203 --> 05:40.707
- Now we can be family again.

05:40.773 --> 05:43.776
{\an1}- I got the poops.
I gotta use the kitchen.

05:43.843 --> 05:46.779
{\an3}- No Fee, that room's not--
we talked about this last time!

05:46.846 --> 05:48.948
- ♪ Doop, doop, doobie, doobie,
doobie, doobie ♪

05:49.015 --> 05:51.017
♪ Doop do-- ♪

05:51.084 --> 05:52.452
- What am I gonna do, Harvey?

05:52.518 --> 05:54.087
They're total weirdoes.

05:54.153 --> 05:57.090
I always imagined my parents
would be more like,

05:57.156 --> 05:59.459
I don't know, your parents.

05:59.525 --> 06:02.662
- Yeah I'll admit,
they're kinda...

06:02.729 --> 06:04.931
both: Poop-a-doop! Poop-a-doop!
Poop-a-doop!

06:04.997 --> 06:06.532
- ...Unexpected.

06:06.599 --> 06:08.367
But they seem really
sweet and nice.

06:08.434 --> 06:10.436
- I don't know anything
about them.

06:10.503 --> 06:12.705
Like, how far can they spit?

06:12.772 --> 06:14.373
What's their favorite
kind of mud?

06:14.440 --> 06:16.442
Are they allergic to pizza?

06:16.509 --> 06:19.645
[sighs] How do I know
they'll be good parents?

06:19.712 --> 06:22.849
- Well, I guess you could
test them.

06:22.915 --> 06:25.051
- Test them how?

06:25.118 --> 06:27.620
- And Foo will bite.
A lot.

06:27.687 --> 06:30.289
{\an1}- It's like
an involuntary reaction.

06:30.356 --> 06:31.524
- Hey Mommy? Daddy?

06:31.591 --> 06:33.259
These people are
here to see you.

06:33.326 --> 06:34.927
- Parent Inspectors.
We heard there were

06:34.994 --> 06:36.929
some long-lost parents
in this house.

06:36.996 --> 06:38.097
- That is us!

06:38.164 --> 06:39.565
- So yeah, we're gonna need you

06:39.632 --> 06:41.033
to come with us for testing.

06:41.100 --> 06:42.568
It's all very official.

06:42.635 --> 06:45.738
{\an3}- Harrumph, harrumph, harrumph.
Harrumph.

06:46.672 --> 06:48.307
- I need you two to
understand that

06:48.374 --> 06:50.276
the finding of our reports
will determine

06:50.343 --> 06:52.278
{\an1}if you're cool enough
to be parents.

06:52.345 --> 06:54.714
- We will do whatever it takes!

06:54.781 --> 06:58.050
{\an1}- It is like old proverb.
If you want something,

06:58.117 --> 07:01.621
you find jellyfish and you
make whisper into his ears.

07:01.687 --> 07:04.056
{\an1}Then you mail jellyfish
to third uncle

07:04.123 --> 07:05.691
who makes jellyfish pie.

07:05.758 --> 07:08.261
{\an1}Then you eat pie
and you know to believe

07:08.327 --> 07:09.729
in your dreams.

07:09.796 --> 07:13.432
{\an1}- Okay one point docked
for weird sayings.

07:13.499 --> 07:15.535
{\an3}- Can I just say
I'm surprised Fee and Harvey

07:15.601 --> 07:16.903
aren't here for this?

07:16.969 --> 07:20.106
{\an3}It's kind of important
you know?

07:20.173 --> 07:22.542
{\an1}- Now the first test
is what we call,

07:22.608 --> 07:26.212
"The First Test."
- What are these?

07:26.279 --> 07:28.147
- Those are supposed
to be your kids.

07:28.214 --> 07:29.682
- [sniffing]

07:29.749 --> 07:33.586
These are not my babies!
- Death to the imposters!

07:33.653 --> 07:35.354
{\an3}- Ahh!

07:35.421 --> 07:37.323
[roars]

07:37.390 --> 07:41.194
- [yelling]

07:41.260 --> 07:44.163
We get many points, yes?

07:44.230 --> 07:46.199
{\an1}- This time we'll use
your real baby.

07:46.265 --> 07:49.602
- Is definitely real.
- We don't have to destroy him.

07:49.669 --> 07:52.271
- Here we have many
food choices.

07:52.338 --> 07:55.408
Cake, salad, cup 'o nails.

07:55.474 --> 07:56.943
{\an1}Which one should
you feed him?

07:57.009 --> 07:58.344
- Oh, that's a easy one.

07:58.411 --> 08:01.214
{\an1}We feed him traditional
jellyfish borscht.

08:01.280 --> 08:06.219
Made from blend of delicious
jellyfish and watery yogurt.

08:06.285 --> 08:08.688
- Mm! Mm-mm! Mm! Mm!

08:08.754 --> 08:11.958
- Shh, this put hair
on your chalakas.

08:12.024 --> 08:15.061
{\an3}- [crying]

08:15.127 --> 08:18.231
- So this next test
is to see how you--

08:18.297 --> 08:20.566
wait, where'd they go?

08:20.633 --> 08:22.001
What are you doing?

08:22.068 --> 08:24.203
{\an1}- I caught a fish so that
we could show you

08:24.270 --> 08:25.771
how good we are at soccer.

08:25.838 --> 08:27.807
- That doesn't even
make any sense.

08:27.874 --> 08:28.908
- [grunts]

08:28.975 --> 08:30.509
- Goal!

08:30.576 --> 08:32.979
- Okay, that's it.
We're done!

08:33.044 --> 08:34.981
- So we pass inspection?

08:35.047 --> 08:37.884
- Why couldn't you just
be like normal parents?

08:37.950 --> 08:40.519
{\an3}Just go back home to your
weirdo country.

08:40.586 --> 08:42.488
Foo and I are fine on our own.

08:42.554 --> 08:45.057
We always have been.

08:47.260 --> 08:49.095
- Wait, that was Fee?

08:49.161 --> 08:51.030
Then who the heck
are you?

08:55.534 --> 08:59.839
<i>- ♪ Life's a daydream ♪</i>
- [giggling]

08:59.906 --> 09:04.777
<i>- ♪ Of fields and soft streams ♪</i>
- Mommy? Mommy?

09:04.844 --> 09:09.515
<i>- ♪ Sunshine, bold leaves ♪</i>

09:09.582 --> 09:16.122
<i>♪ Roots of tall trees ♪</i>

09:16.188 --> 09:18.724
- [gurgling]

09:18.791 --> 09:22.828
<i>- ♪ Hold the hands of those</i>
<i>you love</i>

09:22.895 --> 09:27.633
<i>♪ And tell them the things</i>
<i>that you dream of ♪</i>

09:27.700 --> 09:33.272
<i>♪ Our time moves fast ♪</i>

09:33.339 --> 09:36.275
<i>♪ Warm winds through the grass</i>
<i>by the small stream ♪</i>

09:36.342 --> 09:41.480
<i>♪ Not what it seems</i>
<i>we are what we choose to be ♪</i>

09:41.547 --> 09:44.250
<i>♪ Be free ♪</i>

09:44.317 --> 09:48.054
{\an3}- Fee?
You okay?

09:48.120 --> 09:49.588
- How can I be with them?

09:49.655 --> 09:53.326
{\an1}They left us alone
all those years.

09:53.392 --> 09:55.094
- I guess I don't
see it that way.

09:55.161 --> 09:59.031
'Cause to me, they looked
for us all those years.

10:01.267 --> 10:07.073
- Babies? Babies!
<i>- ♪ Find your way home ♪</i>

10:07.139 --> 10:12.078
both: Babies!
<i>- ♪ You're not alone ♪</i>

10:13.346 --> 10:15.481
both: Babies!

10:16.282 --> 10:18.117
both: Babies!

10:18.184 --> 10:21.220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:21.287 --> 10:26.025
<i>- ♪ Side by side,</i>
<i>we're stronger still ♪</i>

10:26.092 --> 10:30.429
<i>♪ Crickets sing</i>
<i>and campfire spills ♪</i>

10:30.496 --> 10:36.369
<i>♪ Its magic light ♪</i>

10:36.435 --> 10:39.105
<i>♪ Up through the night</i>
<i>by the small stream ♪</i>

10:39.171 --> 10:44.310
<i>♪ Not what it seems,</i>
<i>we are what we choose to be ♪</i>

10:44.377 --> 10:47.113
<i>♪ Be free ♪</i>

10:47.179 --> 10:49.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:49.215 --> 10:50.750
- I hope they like apple,

10:50.816 --> 10:54.954
'cause this pie has
lots of a-peel.

10:55.021 --> 10:56.889
That doesn't
really work with apples.

10:56.956 --> 10:59.091
- Hey, Harvey.
- Oh, Fee!

10:59.158 --> 11:01.527
{\an3}I'm glad you're here.
I need a good apple pun

11:01.594 --> 11:04.430
{\an3}to go with this pie
I made for your parents.

11:04.497 --> 11:08.067
- So um, I'm cool
with my folks now.

11:08.134 --> 11:10.569
{\an3}- So you guys are gonna
be our neighbors now, huh?

11:10.636 --> 11:16.075
{\an1}- Uhh, no. Foo and I
will go home with them.

11:16.142 --> 11:20.513
We're leaving Littlebark.
- What?

11:21.680 --> 11:23.649
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:23.716 --> 11:25.584
- Claire, what are you doing?
- Ahh!

11:25.651 --> 11:27.286
- Harvey's talking over here!

11:27.353 --> 11:28.721
- Good morning everyone.

11:28.788 --> 11:30.389
{\an3}Before we all
enjoy the playground,

11:30.456 --> 11:32.691
I thought it'd be nice to
discuss what we each want

11:32.758 --> 11:34.427
to accomplish with
today's play time.

11:34.493 --> 11:37.496
{\an3}- I wanna get through
one day without crying.

11:37.563 --> 11:39.165
- Everybody look at me!

11:39.231 --> 11:41.233
- Sounds like everyone
wants to have fun,

11:41.300 --> 11:45.704
and my favorite thing about
having fun is following rules.

11:45.771 --> 11:48.207
Rule number one:
always look both ways

11:48.274 --> 11:50.309
when using the slide.

11:52.511 --> 11:53.979
Wow, what a rush.

11:54.046 --> 11:57.316
{\an1}Rule number two:
always share with each other.

11:57.383 --> 12:00.019
Ehh, uhh, uhh, uh.

12:00.086 --> 12:03.255
Rule number three: never swing
past the safety line

12:03.322 --> 12:04.457
I drew on the tree.

12:04.523 --> 12:06.125
The results can be dangerous.

12:06.192 --> 12:08.461
Just ask Kratz.
- Yeah.

12:08.527 --> 12:09.862
And could you
all please not

12:09.929 --> 12:12.031
draw anything explicit
on my cast?

12:12.098 --> 12:15.267
I'm looking at you, Piri.
- Ehhh, ehhh.

12:15.334 --> 12:17.803
- But the most important
rule of all, guys,

12:17.870 --> 12:19.472
just remember to have fun!

12:19.538 --> 12:20.840
[all cheering]

12:20.906 --> 12:23.375
- Carefully, very carefully.

12:27.146 --> 12:31.383
Hey!
You don't belong there, mister.

12:31.450 --> 12:33.619
Boop.
- [screaming]

12:33.686 --> 12:35.221
[grunting]

12:35.287 --> 12:38.124
- My leaves!
What is that?

12:40.426 --> 12:43.496
{\an1}Hello?
Are you okay--ow!

12:43.562 --> 12:46.532
{\an1}Ow, ow, ow, ow,
ay, ah, ah!

12:46.599 --> 12:47.800
[growls]

12:47.867 --> 12:50.202
[grunting]

12:53.739 --> 12:56.175
No! Not my dry erase board!

12:58.310 --> 12:59.378
- Ehh?

13:02.381 --> 13:05.050
[yelling]

13:05.117 --> 13:06.819
[moaning]

13:06.886 --> 13:09.255
[snores] Ah.

13:09.321 --> 13:11.957
- Uh! [grunting]

13:12.024 --> 13:13.926
- [growls] Uh, uh!

13:13.993 --> 13:16.729
- Ah! Oh! Ah!
[panting]

13:16.795 --> 13:19.165
- [roars] Mm!

13:20.833 --> 13:22.201
- Aw, you poor thing.

13:22.268 --> 13:24.703
{\an1}Why don't you want
to wash up in the bathtub?

13:24.770 --> 13:26.872
{\an3}- And track mud
all over the house?

13:26.939 --> 13:28.507
I just shampooed the floors!

13:28.574 --> 13:31.377
Who just throws mud
at someone they don't even know?

13:31.443 --> 13:33.846
- When I was a kid,
I had plenty of reasons

13:33.913 --> 13:35.314
to throw mud at people.

13:35.381 --> 13:38.584
If I was hungry
or if I'd just eaten.

13:38.651 --> 13:40.719
- Yeah, your Mom
was terrifying.

13:40.786 --> 13:42.154
{\an3}You know, you should
go and tell them

13:42.221 --> 13:43.722
that they hurt your feelings.

13:43.789 --> 13:46.859
- I don't ever know
where they live.

13:46.926 --> 13:49.428
- Guys, there are two
small creatures

13:49.495 --> 13:51.096
stealing our recycling bins.

13:51.163 --> 13:54.400
- That's them! Okay, I'm gonna
go tell them how I feel.

13:54.466 --> 13:58.170
{\an1}- Remember that jiu-jitsu move
I showed you, sweetie.

13:59.471 --> 14:02.107
- Hello?
Excuse me?

14:02.174 --> 14:02.942
Ugh! Ooh!

14:03.008 --> 14:04.710
How about we start over?

14:04.777 --> 14:07.646
- [growling]
- My name is Harvey.

14:07.713 --> 14:10.683
Har-vey.

14:10.749 --> 14:12.351
- We can understand you, stupid.

14:12.418 --> 14:15.821
- Oh. Well, I just wanted
to say that you

14:15.888 --> 14:17.923
really hurt my feelings
earlier when you--

14:17.990 --> 14:20.025
{\an3}- [mocking] And I just wanna
say you hurt my feelings

14:20.092 --> 14:21.560
meh, meh, meh, meh.

14:21.627 --> 14:24.029
- Hey! Stop that!
- [mocking] Hey, stop that!

14:24.096 --> 14:26.498
- I mean it! Or I'll--ahh!

14:26.565 --> 14:28.200
- Or you'll what?

14:28.267 --> 14:30.970
{\an8}- Or we'll have to go through
the official handbook

14:31.036 --> 14:34.840
of conflict mediation
in its entirety.

14:34.907 --> 14:36.942
{\an1}- I was wrong about you.
You're not a threat.

14:37.009 --> 14:39.011
{\an1}You're just boring.
Let's get outta here.

14:39.078 --> 14:41.547
- Hey, wait, we haven't
resolved our conflict!

14:41.614 --> 14:45.184
{\an3}- Dude, buzz off.
You're bugging us. Right, Foo?

14:45.251 --> 14:46.118
{\an1}- Ahh!

14:46.185 --> 14:49.788
Ahh! I stubbed my toe.

14:49.855 --> 14:52.124
- Ooh, that looks like it hurt.

14:52.191 --> 14:55.361
- [spits] There.
- No, it still hurts.

14:55.427 --> 14:58.364
Ow! Ow! Ow!
- There we go.

14:58.430 --> 15:01.634
- Um, that's not goo--
- Ahh!

15:01.700 --> 15:03.135
Screaming at it will help!

15:03.202 --> 15:05.271
Ahh!
- Wait, just come with me.

15:05.337 --> 15:07.506
I have some medicine and snacks
at my house.

15:07.573 --> 15:09.975
- Yeah right. We don't wanna go
anywhere with you.

15:10.042 --> 15:12.745
Right, Foo?
- Umm, well...

15:12.811 --> 15:15.781
what kinda snacks
do you have?

15:15.848 --> 15:18.584
- There we go, nice and snug.

15:18.651 --> 15:20.719
- Who wants some orange juice?
- I do!

15:20.786 --> 15:23.455
- Harvey said you two
were new to Littlebark.

15:23.522 --> 15:26.992
- Uh yeah.

15:27.059 --> 15:29.061
- Why don't you tell us
a bit about yourselves?

15:29.128 --> 15:32.398
- I don't know.
I'm Fee, he's Foo.

15:32.464 --> 15:34.199
- Ooh!

15:34.266 --> 15:37.202
{\an1}- Well, Fee, Foo,
we're going to have dinner.

15:37.269 --> 15:40.005
{\an1}Would you like to call your
parents and see if you can stay?

15:40.072 --> 15:41.273
- It's taco night!

15:41.340 --> 15:44.476
- Uhh, we don't have parents.

15:45.678 --> 15:48.480
- What do you mean?
- I don't know.

15:48.547 --> 15:51.083
We just don't have parents.
What? Is that weird?

15:51.150 --> 15:54.386
- Oh.
- But who takes care of you?

15:55.254 --> 15:58.390
- It's just me and Foo.

15:59.758 --> 16:02.661
- I'm sorry.

16:02.728 --> 16:04.530
- Foo and I have to go.

16:04.596 --> 16:05.864
{\an3}- Bye!

16:05.931 --> 16:07.566
- Well, wait!

16:07.633 --> 16:09.668
[door closes]

16:18.677 --> 16:25.918
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:37.062 --> 16:40.265
[both spitting]

16:42.201 --> 16:45.471
- [spits] Eh!

16:46.705 --> 16:49.641
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

16:49.708 --> 16:56.949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:58.650 --> 17:00.886
- Whee!

17:00.953 --> 17:03.188
- Ahh!

17:04.256 --> 17:06.992
[both laughing]
- Whoo-hoo!

17:13.065 --> 17:15.300
{\an1}- Uh-uh.

17:16.167 --> 17:18.837
- This was fun! You guys wanna
hang out tomorrow?

17:18.904 --> 17:22.107
- Uhh, yeah, sure.

17:22.174 --> 17:24.643
- I'm really glad
we're friends now.

17:27.246 --> 17:30.115
[wind gusting]

17:30.182 --> 17:32.818
{\an1}Wow.
I'm really gonna miss you guys.

17:32.885 --> 17:34.219
- Where are you going?

17:34.286 --> 17:36.388
{\an3}Oh, right.
We're leaving.

17:36.455 --> 17:40.125
- Mom and Dad said we should
get back home in a few days.

17:40.192 --> 17:41.894
- Fee and Foo! Come see!
- Look at this!

17:41.960 --> 17:43.495
- We made you a farewell card!

17:43.562 --> 17:45.831
- Sorry it says,
"Happy Retirement."

17:45.898 --> 17:48.367
You can blame Kratz for that.

17:48.434 --> 17:51.537
{\an1}- I stitched the banner
with me and Claire's hair.

17:51.603 --> 17:53.005
- Wait, What?!

17:53.071 --> 17:54.673
- Aye! Bye, Felica!
<i>[dance music]</i>

17:54.740 --> 17:57.843
Oh shoot, was that the card?
Guys, my bad.

17:57.910 --> 17:59.311
[both laughing]

17:59.378 --> 18:02.047
- Stop!
I have prepared a statement.

18:02.114 --> 18:04.149
[clears throat]
"Dear Fee and Foo,

18:04.216 --> 18:06.151
"I wish you
were both in jail.

18:06.218 --> 18:08.454
"You stole my best friend,
you smell,

18:08.520 --> 18:10.022
"and you're both trash people.

18:10.088 --> 18:12.324
I do not like you at all.
Good-bye."

18:12.391 --> 18:13.992
- That's all I have to say.

18:14.059 --> 18:17.362
- Can we have a hug?
- Yeah, okay.

18:17.429 --> 18:19.498
{\an7}- We will haunt
your dreams forever!

18:19.565 --> 18:22.401
{\an8}- [whispering] Forever.
- [scoffs]

18:22.468 --> 18:24.803
{\an1}- Hey! You didn't think
we'd let you go

18:24.870 --> 18:26.672
{\an1}without saying good-bye,
did you?

18:26.738 --> 18:28.507
- I'm gonna miss your faces.

18:28.574 --> 18:30.776
{\an1}- Hey, you're all
welcome back anytime.

18:30.843 --> 18:34.279
{\an1}- Absolutely, you're
part of our family now, too.

18:34.346 --> 18:36.014
- Hug sandwich!

18:36.081 --> 18:38.417
- Delicious food you
feed us is starting

18:38.484 --> 18:40.452
to disagree with belly.

18:40.519 --> 18:43.489
We go now.
- We will say good-bye

18:43.555 --> 18:47.459
with our most sacred
of farewell rituals.

18:47.526 --> 18:48.827
- I kick you.
- Oh!

18:48.894 --> 18:50.295
- And I kick you!
- Oh!

18:50.362 --> 18:52.464
You're welcome.
- Hey Michelle,

18:52.531 --> 18:54.099
next time I see you,
we're gonna get

18:54.166 --> 18:56.201
those face tattoos
we talked about.

18:58.670 --> 19:00.539
{\an3}Nice!

19:00.606 --> 19:04.910
- All right, sun is setting
and wolves come soon.

19:04.977 --> 19:06.311
- Is time for leaving!

19:06.378 --> 19:08.547
{\an1}- Mom, Dad, don't forget
the travel bag.

19:08.614 --> 19:11.950
{\an3}- Oh yes.
So good you remembered.

19:12.017 --> 19:14.620
{\an1}- Without these,
we all die painfully.

19:14.686 --> 19:18.757
{\an3}You are very responsible,
my babies!

19:18.824 --> 19:21.894
- Well, I guess this is it.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.996
Oh, I almost forgot.

19:24.062 --> 19:26.164
Here. I made you
a letter writing kit

19:26.231 --> 19:28.634
so we can stay in touch.

19:28.700 --> 19:30.869
- [munching]

19:30.936 --> 19:32.971
{\an1}- Oh! I thought
that would happen.

19:33.038 --> 19:36.608
So I made some extras!
- Thanks for the snack, Harvey!

19:36.675 --> 19:39.211
Tastes like paper.
- Bye Harvey!

19:39.278 --> 19:40.579
- [whimpers]

19:40.646 --> 19:41.580
{\an3}- Harvey.

19:41.647 --> 19:42.781
- What?

19:42.848 --> 19:44.182
- Harvey!

19:44.249 --> 19:46.885
- What?
[crying]

19:46.952 --> 19:48.320
- Harvey.

19:48.387 --> 19:50.188
Foo, help me out, here.

19:50.255 --> 19:53.992
- [blubbering]
I'm gonna miss you.

19:54.059 --> 19:57.696
{\an3}- You know what?
Come here!

19:57.763 --> 20:00.165
{\an3}Okay, bye.

20:00.232 --> 20:01.900
Thanks for everything!

20:01.967 --> 20:03.535
- Have safe travels!
- I'm gonna miss you guys!

20:03.602 --> 20:05.637
- Be safe, Fee and Foo.
- Bye!

20:05.704 --> 20:08.440
<i>[somber music]</i>

20:08.507 --> 20:11.209
- Good-bye, Fee.
Good-bye, Foo.

20:11.276 --> 20:16.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:16.448 --> 20:19.051
{\an1}- Honey, you didn't
come down for dinner.

20:19.117 --> 20:22.554
- I--I don't know what
to do.

20:22.621 --> 20:24.189
I'm happy they found
their family,

20:24.256 --> 20:27.159
but why'd they have to leave?

20:27.225 --> 20:29.061
Why can't they stay forever

20:29.127 --> 20:31.463
like you guys or Michelle?

20:31.530 --> 20:33.432
{\an3}- Sometimes people come
into your life

20:33.498 --> 20:35.367
{\an3}and sometimes they
have to leave.

20:35.434 --> 20:38.136
- That's so sad.
- It is sad.

20:38.203 --> 20:40.105
But you're also really lucky

20:40.172 --> 20:41.573
you got to be their friend.

20:41.640 --> 20:44.209
{\an1}Nothing's ever
going to change that.

20:44.276 --> 20:47.212
<i>[hopeful music]</i>

20:47.279 --> 20:48.614
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:48.680 --> 20:51.617
<i>- Yeah.</i>
<i>You found each other.</i>

20:51.683 --> 20:54.019
<i>When a friend comes</i>
<i>into your life,</i>

20:54.086 --> 20:55.954
<i>it changes you a little.</i>

20:56.021 --> 20:59.825
<i>They challenge you.</i>
<i>They make you laugh.</i>

20:59.891 --> 21:01.960
<i>They make you stronger.</i>

21:02.027 --> 21:04.429
<i>Each person gives you a gift.</i>

21:04.496 --> 21:09.267
<i>A special part of them</i>
<i>that you keep forever.</i>

21:09.334 --> 21:11.637
{\an8}<i>It's like they're</i>
<i>always with you.</i>

21:11.703 --> 21:18.744
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:37.929 --> 21:44.970
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:01.953 --> 22:04.890
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

22:04.956 --> 22:11.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>
